\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Expansionary policy: one GDP point-increase of public spending
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We first simulate the medium and long term impact of an expantionary policy:
 a one GDP point-increase of public spending.
 Since, governement spending at the base year accounts for about one quarter
 of the GDP, this shock correponds to an increase of 4% of public expenditure.
 The proportion of this impulse in terms of products is proportional to
 the base year public consumption:
